      <hedline>
        <hl1>Thoughts on Thinking</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Brotshner letter finds it hardly surprising that fulture influences how people think (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It came as absolutely no surprise to me when I read that culture influences the way people think (''How Culture Molds Habits of Thoughts'').</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It came as absolutely no surprise to me when I read that culture influences the way people think (''How Culture Molds Habits of Thoughts'').</p>
        <p>I was especially unfazed by the finding that ''Easterners'' and ''Westerners'' employ different cognitive processes: I've lived in California for two years now, after a lifetime in New York, and I still can't figure these people out!</p>
        <p>MICHAEL BROTCHNER  San Francisco</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
